.TH FESTIVALD "1" "July 2018" "festivald version @festivald_version@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
festivald \- a unix socket daemon for festival, the speech synthesis system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B festivald [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fB\-q\fR
.IP
Do not load default festival setup files
.PP
\fB\-\-libdir\fR <string>
.IP
Set festival library directory path
.PP
\fB\-\-socket\fR <string>
.IP
Socket path. It should be in a directory with restricted permissions
(if the socket is "systemd" uses systemd socket activation)
.PP
\fB\-\-max\-clients\fR <int> {10}
.IP
Max. number of clients allowed to connect to the server
.PP
\fB\-\-heap\fR <int> {10000000}
.IP
Set size of Lisp heap, should not normally need
to be changed from its default
.PP
\fB\-v | -version \fR
.IP
Display version number and exit
.PP
